modules.description: This module implements SMTP client operations for sending email messages over Unix sockets, handling connection setup, TLS encryption, and message submission. It works with low-level data structures like `Colombe` types for email addresses and `Ke.Rke.t` for queues, along with TLS and authentication configurations. Concrete use cases include programmatically sending emails with custom headers, handling delivery errors, and managing secure SMTP connections with optional client authentication.
